LINE.Text: ARMED TO THE TEETH

controversial clauses in history. Gun supporters have invoked it to make the case for owning firearms while others
have cited it to encourage more stringent anti-gun laws. Regardless, gun ownership in the United States remains

last few years, trends have been showing a very evenly divided public, with slightly more Americans
now favoring the right to own firearms.
